definitions.definition: A person who makes frames for paintings .
A person who assembles the frame of a ship .
A person who assembles the timbers of a wood-framed building.
A person who writes a new law .

subdefinitions.definition: Any of the delegates to the Constitutional Convention that drafted the United States Constitution and the Bill of Rights .
subdefinitions.label_groups: historical , US politics , sometimes capitalized , usually in the plural

definitions.definition: A person who frames another, attempting to have them convicted of a crime they did not commit.
A person who embeds another person's web pages in an HTML frame , so that they misleadingly appear to be part of the framing site.

main_definition: A person who makes frames for paintings .
